          <text>
                    <body>
                              <p rend="align(right)"><date>1844</date>.</p>
                              <p rend="align(right)"><placeName>Alpen</placeName>,
                                                  <date>Friday</date>, pericope Vaylkran,
                                        (Maron[?])<lb/></p>
                              <p>May there be great peace, mercy and kindness to my nephew, the wise<lb/>
                                        <persName>Isaac</persName>, etc.,</p>
                              <p rend="indent(1)">I have one more request to make of you, namely
                                        that I still<lb/> look forward to your sending me that which
                                        you have promised me more than<lb/> two whole years ago.
                                        Even though it is across the sea, do not say, "Who<lb/> will
                                        cross it for us?". Only let the road be near in your heart
                                        to do it.*<lb/> Believe me, upon my word of honor, that if I
                                        did not find myself <sic>ina</sic> bad<lb/> position, I
                                        would not send you this any more at the present time, at
                                        least not<lb/> put in such a tone, since my letter of a year
                                        ago, in the spring, has re-<lb/>mained unnoticed and
                                        unanswered. I have not been compensated with a few lines
                                        even<lb/> for my postage expense. Even if my request
                                        remained unfulfilled, it<lb/> would still have been very
                                        pleasant to have been able to say that I had<lb/> received a
                                        letter from my relative in <placeName>America</placeName>.
                                        But this, too, was not<lb/> granted me. Well, then, dear
                                                  <persName>Itzik</persName>, if you want to fulfill
                                        your promise,<lb/> do it now or not at all, and show that
                                        you still have some regard for<lb/> your old uncle. My
                                        position is already known to you from my previous<lb/>
                                        letter. It has become worse rather than better. What is
                                        more, I find<lb/> it quite unnecessary to expose to you my
                                        entire present situation. You<lb/> know it well enough if
                                        you want <sic>tohelp</sic>.</p>
                              <p rend="indent(1)">Recently, I read about you in the "Zeitung des
                                        Judentums",<lb/> by <persName>Dr. Philippson</persName>,
                                        that you are [?]uiting a monthly. This proves that you<lb/>
                                        are in correspondence with <placeName>Europe</placeName>.
                                        You can therefore direct a few lines<lb/> to me, even though
                                        you may not be able or willing to help me. My family<lb/> in
                                                  <placeName>Dülmen</placeName>,
                                                  <placeName>Rheine</placeName>, and
                                                  <placeName>Barmen</placeName> are all, thank God,
                                        in good health. I hope<lb/> to hear the same from you as
                                        soon as possible. That is my most fervent<lb/> wish.</p>
                              <p rend="indent(1)">With wishes for your life, and peace, and length
                                        of days<lb/> and years, from the ever-living God, I remain
                                        as ever,</p>
                              <p rend="indent(2)">Your uncle <persName role="author"
                                                  >Abraham</persName>, son of</p>
                              <p rend="indent(3)">
                                        <persName>Eliesar Leeser</persName>
                              </p>
                              <p>* Up to this point in Hebrew, based on Deuteronomy 30:12-13.</p>
